2. Resample¶

DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].resample("M").plot()

In [13]:
DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].resample("2W").mean().plot()

In [54]:
DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].resample("2W").std().plot()
plt.show()
In [53]:
plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].plot()
DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].resample("M").mean().plot(label="moyenne par mois", lw=3, ls=":", alpha=0.8)
DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].resample("W").mean().plot(label="moyenne par semaine", lw=2, ls="--", alpha=0.8)
plt.legend()
plt.show()

3. Aggregate¶

In [55]:
m = DAX["Close"].resample("6W").agg(["mean", "std", "min", "max"])

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
m["mean"]["2021"].plot(label="moyenne par semaine")
plt.fill_between(m.index, m["max"], m["min"], alpha=0.2, label="min-max par semaine")

plt.legend()
plt.show()
In [56]:
_ = DAX.loc["2021", "Close"].resample("5W").agg(["mean", "std", "min", "max"]).plot()

4. Moving Average et EWM¶

In [57]:
plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
DAX.loc["2021-09", "Close"].plot()
DAX.loc["2021-09", "Close"].rolling(window=7).mean().plot(label="non centre", lw=3, ls=":", alpha=0.8)
DAX.loc["2021-09", "Close"].rolling(window=7, center=True).mean().plot(label="centre", lw=3, ls=":", alpha=0.8)
DAX.loc["2021-09", "Close"].ewm(alpha=0.6).mean().plot(label="ewm", lw=3, ls=":", alpha=0.8)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
In [58]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
DAX.loc["2021-09", "Close"].plot()
for i in np.arange(0.2, 1, 0.2):
    DAX.loc["2021-09", "Close"].ewm(alpha=i).mean().plot(label=f"ewm {i}", ls="--", alpha=0.8)
plt.legend()
plt.show()
